sentences: She made her debut at Ella's Second Subscription concert in 1831, and sang regularly at Philharmonic Society Concerts.
She founded the Royal Society of Female Musicians in 1839, and died in London.
Elizabeth Masson (1806 – 9 January 1865) was an English mezzo-soprano singer and composer.
She was born in Scotland and studied singing with Mrs. Henry Smart and Giuditta Pasta in Italy.
